<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="902" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d902">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 150.07/21</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Russian Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bakhméteff</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russian Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Newport, Rhode Island</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-27">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3:30 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>I would be much obliged to you if you would give immediate instructions
                            to immigration authorities on Canadian border to allow admission of
                            Russians to New York in transit to Archangel by steamer sailing
                            Saturday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bakhméteff</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>